  "texts": [
    "This approach was adopted due to the potential divergence from the evaluation of ToM proficiency to a broader assessment of language comprehension.",
    "For example, responding to the unexpected content task by suggesting that the sister would anticipate the presence of pencils in the box signifies a deficiency in ToM.",
    "Conversely, answering in a manner suggesting she would assume they are stickers or choosing not to respond at all implies challenges in grasping the entirety of the conversation, indicative of broader difficulties in comprehending the overall discourse.",
    "Average values of the observed metrics are presented along with their 95% confidence intervals (using bootstrap resampling for numeric variables and exact binomial confidence intervals for analyzing categorical variables).",
    "These confidence intervals are valid only when sampling from the same model under identical conditions since even slight changes in the prompt can lead to significant variations in outcomes, as highlighted by [62]."
  ],
